<summary>
The <strong><c>placeholder</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement"/> interface represents a hint to the user of what can be entered in the control. It reflects the {{htmlelement("textarea")}} element's <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea#placeholder"><c>placeholder</c></see> attribute.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea">textarea</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement.Value"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTextAreaElement/placeholder"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A string.</value>
